title: Tin is reusable by kids who love cupcakes
text: I recently sent two of these as birthday gifts and the Mom got the loaded gift cards with instructions to let the kids have the tins since I could not bring them edible cupcakes.  From purchases in the past, I was aware that they are pretty thin in depth as well as the metal gauge and I knew that there is a clear plastic rectangle on the rear which provides Amazon to identify the code on the card inside of the tin.  The kids didn't mind that and the Mom didn't mind sharing her gift.  I suspect that the funds embedded in the cards eventually went to buying items for the kids anyway because she's a sharing person.  This is one of my favorite physical gift cards from Amazon which I enjoy sending.

title: It's a gift card inside a metal box with a plastic insert
text: The gift card works.  You apply it to your account and have the funds to cover a purchase up to the dollar amount of the value applied to the card.  You cannot add to the card, once it's applied to the account, the card is useless as a form of tender.  I personally have a tool to make guitar picks from cards like these, so I'll make a couple of guitar picks from this one and give them to the kids.  One of the kids loves to play his guitar.  The tin in which it arrives has a cutout with a plastic insert so that the warehouse workers know which card to select to fulfill the order, and that does not hinder my using the tin for other things.  I actually like to see what's inside the box, just like the Amazon staff I guess.

title: Physical card is sometimes preferred
text: It's a gift card in a small box with an orange ribbon and bow on the box top. You can send an Amazon gift card by email or hand deliver one like this. They all work the same, money which is applied to a person's Amazon account.  Only problem I have with gift cards is that purchases don't register as "verified purchase" when the gift card balance is used for payment and you leave a review.

title: Pay attention if you purchase with an incentive
text: I like having a gift card balance from which payment is made for small ticket items and tend to uncheck the box for applying a gift card balance for purchases where a credit card payment is more beneficial, as when an extended warranty is offered.  Since this has no expiration date, I find that it allows me to save time when balancing my credit card statements at the end of the month, particularly since I can check my gift card balance and see exactly when and for what amount the payment was made.  When Amazon offers an incentive to reload is when I typically make my purchases, and although it has not applied the additional amount instantaneously, I have found that after a phone call, it miraculously tends to appear.  For this reason, I have to deduct a star from my review.

title: They Like To Choose Their Own Gift
text:
It's probably more fun for me to buy a gift, wrap it and deliver it in person.

It's probably more fun for the recipient to receive money or a gift card so that they can choose their own item.

You can never go wrong with money; a gift card is -- to me anyway -- slightly classier than money. And Amazon.com has a wide enough selection of items that the recipient can usually find SOMETHING; growing wider every day, too.

Once, or twice, a year (birthdays and/or Christmas) I like to give my friend's children a little something. And they seem to LOVE receiving gift cards from Amazon.com!

title: Olive Garden overcharged their customers for worst food they made
text:
Olive Garden overcharged their customers for worst food they made. Upon arrival at a local Olive Garden branch in October 2014, my friends and I saw only a few customers sit there so we should be assigned a seat quickly. There were several welcoming representatives just talking to each other and one told us that we had to wait at least 20 minutes to get seated.

After the dirty and sour meal, we were overcharged and were forced to pay 20% service fee as tips. If it's a good meal and service, we might pay more than 30% of dinner price as tip but we had a horrible dining experience in Olive Garden. After all, we would never visit Olive Garden again because such a bad restaurant kept ripping people off. I have seen bad reviews on this restaurant from other people on other sites too.

title: Gift card joy
text: Its a gift card to amazon, what could possibly be wrong?  That being said we order this on a Wednesday night (with like 4 minutes left to get it shipped next day) and it was at my house the next evening.  Amazing if you ask me (and it shipped next day for free--- HOW does Amazon do it?)  I work in a company that ships product all over the world and I can't see how they can turn a profit on a deal like this (actually I do know how they do it- but it is a real tight margin on a deal like this)

title: Who Doesn't Like an Amazon Gift Card???
text: I like to switch up on gift cards, buying some as a "print at home" and others being delivered physically to my mailbox. The cards that come in the gift card tin or envelope always look a bit classier than the print at home. And gifting via email is so impersonal. Holding a card on a special occasion is so much more satisfying.

title: Perfect for Graduate
text: This is the cutest gift box for a graduate and it hit the mark when trying to fancy up an Amazon gift card for a recent graduate. Came well protected and was a hit.

title: Teenagers will thank you!
text: Each year we get a family member an Amazon or Kindle card. As she has grown up, it went from Kindle branded to Amazon branded - now she wants her own Amazon Prime account at 17 ; /  Anyway, I rate this 5 stars because she can use it for anything she wants through Amazon, but Amazon will need to update its stock of tins or next year a star knocked off for not updating or refreshing its designs. I want to give the Amazon tin instead of email or print because it eludes to a personal touch (even if all done from my laptop). We've given every available tin and next year will hope for a new design. (Yes, carbon footprint exists with giving physical cards, but darn it we're old fashioned when it comes to Christmas!). Always a winner!

My oldest son just turned 39 and I was able to load it with $39 -- a tradition I have for birthdays for my kids and others close to family. He really liked the mock-up tiny Amazon box it came in. title: Makes for a Nice Gift for Olive Garden Fans
text: Nice gift for family members and friends who like Olive Garden.  This forces them to go out and have a good time.  And maybe they will take you with them!  I bought Olive Garden gift card for a family member today.

title: Fun Gift
text: If you know someone who like Olive Garden, this is a fun gift to give them.  It makes them treat themselves and splurge a little bit.  And maybe they will take you with them when they go to Olive Garden.

title: A Treat for the Holiday!
text: My son and daughter-in-law work full time in a small midwestern town.  There aren't many restaurants in town, but there's a Domino Pizza.  So, when they don't want to cook, or have students over - my son is a professor - they can serve up some classic Domino Pizza.  Figured this would give them an excuse to not cook and have a break.  I called the Domino's in their town as recommended to ensure they take gift cards and they do!  My daughter-in-law likes this pizza, so figured these gift cards would make her happy!

title: Attractive Gift Card Package
text: This gift box is very attractive for the gift card.  I bought this Cracker Barrel card for my son who is saving money for the future and doesn't splurge very often to go out. I like to give gift cards to restaurants as you are buying someone an experience, a bit of deliciousness and fun to break up the routine of home-cooked meals. The box is included free with the gift cards, which is great.  You don't have to wrap the cards and it makes for an attractive gift.  You can recycle the box for other gift cards.

title: Give A Tasty Experience
text: We enjoyed the Italian food we had here.  My son is using this company to cater his wedding reception.  This is a great gift card to get for family members and friends if you have a Buca Di Beppo near you.  Like to give gift cards to eateries as it gives loved ones an experience to savor, rather than more stuff for their house.  If you get the card for your spouse or significant other, good chance they will invite you to accompany them here.

title: Multipack = Multigift
text: This is an original gift to give with Starbux multiple cards.  The receiver can keep some in the car, their wallet or give them to family members. I like to give some to the mail lady for delivering all of those Amazon packages in the snow and ice.

title: Great Gift
text: This is a great gift idea for someone to splurge on some healthy and tasty food. Our local Whole Foods in Connecticut has a short order station where you can get delicious hamburgers, hot dogs, sweet potato friends and shakes to eat in the store at a reasonable price. There's a great soup, salad and entree section and pizza dispensary, too. On Wednesdays, you can buy one soup and get the other at discount. It's an adventure shopping at Whole Foods. These gift cards are a great gift to give someone a quality shopping and eating experience, rather than just more stuff for their home.

title: Like This Gift Card Option
text: Love to get and give gift cards to favorite eateries as it compels you to go out.  We like Paneras soups and sandwiches.  The tomato and broccoli and cheese soup are our favorites.  This is a pleasant eatery for a light and quick meal which is healthier than most fast food.  Love to give these to family members, as sometimes they invite you along to enjoy the card with them.  It's great that Amazon has so many choices like this restaurant among their gift card selections.  When family and friends have enough stuff, giving a gift card for an experience like this makes a thoughtful gift.

title: Love Gift Cards to This Restaurant
text: Love to give restaurant gift cards to family members as you sometimes get to accompany them when they use the card!  And if any of your family is frugal, the card compels them to go out and have a little fun.  Love this restaurant.  Went there tonight.  Their hamburgers are great, as is the side garden salad.  We also sampled a raspberry white chocolate truffle cheesecake.  Yum!  Will be ordering these cards for Father's Day.

title: Love This Gift Card
text: Love to get this gift card for relatives and friends.  Who can't find something tasty at Starbucks and it's fun to pop in there to treat yourself during the day.  Your relatives and friends will think of you each time they use the card.  Good to remind them to register the card with Starbucks in case it gets lost.  I got this for my mail lady as a thank you for bringing all of those Amazon boxes up to the door in the winter and rain.  It's a great gift to send to a loved one.

When you get a gift card to Amazon, you are getting the best shopping and selection that no one can beat.
No matter the amount of the card, you can apply it to your account and use it as needed or allow the total to grow. Get your perfect gift for that special someone, occasion or for you.

title: The Perfect gift from Amazon for Any Occasion.
text:
Gift cards from Amazon are the best gifts that anyone can get for any occasion and any amount..
No matter the box / tin size that it comes in. I got a gift card this past year and I love it. One of the best ideas that anyone can do with a gift card is to allow the gift card balance to grow and when you need anything from Amazon, you can use that gift card balance to the items we need.

I remember a time when I used my gift cards to get a chair mat that was expensive. The gift card balance covered completely the chair mat so I pad nothing. That is why I love gift cards from Amazon.

title: Ah! What I always need.. An Amazon Gift Card.
text:

Whether it's a birthday or holiday use these as a last minute gift. Any amount is welcome to your Amazon account.

title: Another Perfect Gift Idea From Amazon

Nothing says it better than a gift card from Amazon in any amount. I love them. They make a good gift idea for any occasion or for just because. I am planning to get gift cards for the future.

If you need a gift idea this will fill the bill.

title: The Perfect Gift for Any Occasion. Amazon Gift Cards.

title: Money takes a few minutes to get there.
text: What am I reviewing?  This is not a product... this is an Amazon function where I can put money into my Amazon balance... as long as my money goes directly to my balance, what is there for me to review here?  One interesting thing to note is that I can use my Amazon gift card balance to reload my Amazon gift card balance... get your head around that.

title: Convert gift cards to Amazon
text: Sometimes I get gifts in the form of Visa and MasterCard branded cards.  Since these have exact amounts, they are not easy to use at brick & mortar stores.  I use the full amount of these to reload my Amazon balance.  My one complaint is that sometimes it takes a very long time, maybe an hour or longer for the balance to show up on my Amazon account.

title: Thanks for another great item Amazon!
text:
This is awesome! I ordered five different cards - all the same amount - but with different Packaging. This is for a raffle For an upcoming fundraiser.

The little black box with the gold bow was wrapped in plastic And arrived safe without any damage.

The card inside is plastic. it is not heavy paper like some have complained. But I ordered a standard amount and not a different amount.

The box is cute, and yes has a small window on the back showing the UPC barcode. Some have complained about this. But honestly, what else would you expect to get in a small box like this? They've complained that the receiver would know it is a gift card, but what else would be in this size box? It's only a half inch thick for crying out loud!

Ordered on a Saturday and they were shipped overnight and arrived on a Sunday without any problems! May have been related to my Amazon Prime membership.

title: Awesome and these will be great for my fundraiser raffle...!
text:
another great purchase I am very happy with.

I bought five different gift cards in different boxes for the same $100 amount. All are plastic cards. Some reviews have complained about thick paper gift cards instead of plastic. Maybe they purchased non-standard amounts?

The little metal tin is cute with the textured diamond plate pattern. I have no problems with the small window on the back of the box, that shows the UPC codes. Some have complained about that, as then the receiver knows it's a gift card. But what else would come in a little metal box a half inch deep?

Ordered these on a Saturday and receive them the next day - Sunday. Free overnight shipping may have been because my Amazon Prime membership, but still

title: Awesome! Will make my fundraiser great!
text:
A great deal and a great bargain!

I'm hosting a fundraiser and I'm using 5 Amazon gift cards as part of a raffle prize. I ordered five different types of cards so that it could be unique.

Some have complained that their gift card was a thick paper card when the it arrived. It could well be that for non-standard amounts, Amazon doesn't have the little plastic cards printed.

The little metal tin is cute, and nobody would mistake the fact that it does not hold a gift card. some have complained about the window on the back of the box where you can the barcodes and such. My question to you is what else would come in a little box a half inch deep?

Item shipped overnight and arrived on a Sunday. not sure if it is because I am an Amazon Prime member or not.

title: well received & put to good use
text: Kohl's $50. Gift Card:  It was a great gift for a coworker because there are multiple Kohl's nearby. Recipient reported no problems using the card. As with any gift cards, I recommended placing a discrete identifying mark on them, so that a cashier can't (accidentally) claim that you have a $0 balance and then hand you back a different card that REALLY is empty. Keep them in sight for the entire transaction if at all possible!

title: Tamper proof sealed. Gift box moved smoothly!
text:
I bought this for our family's Christmas white elephant gift exchange this year. I put this with a big tub of Lysol wipes in a gift bag. It seemed fitting for 2020. I wanted to gift something that anyone could use, and an Amazon giftcard seemed like the best way to do that. My husband gifted the new Amazon Echo dot, and honestly, our gifts were the only one's that were traded! The gift card was traded the most at 4 times, so I felt good knowing that the giftcard was a good way to go this year. I think we all can use one right now.

This giftcard came in a sealed plastic wrapper, so you know that it's not been tampered with. There's also a receipt that shows the giftcard amount and I recommend that this should be put with the giftcard when gifting, just in case any issues arise when they're redeeming. My dad actually ended up with the giftcard, so I will update if he has any issues. Our giftcard box came in good shape. It moved up & down smoothly and didn't have any noticeable creases anywhere in person. The one thing I wish it had was the giftcard amount listed on the giftcard itself. Aside from the receipt, there's no amount listed anywhere, so we had to write $20 on the back with a marker. Not the most presentable way, but we needed something that could be seen easily so the white elephant game could continue with ease. I seen that other reviewer's giftcards had the total on the upper corner of the giftcard itself, so that's what I was expecting. Amazon giftcards ordered online rarely have that, so I wasn't completely expecting it, but hoping this one would be different. This is one thing that would be a great addition to all Amazon giftcards. I've ordered one from almost every listing on here, and that's the one thing that's been a bit aggravating each time. I folded the receipt and stuffed it behind the black giftcard. These are not the shiny plastic giftcards. These, like almost all of the giftcards bought on here, are a thick card stock material. Most people probably don't care if they're just going to load &dispose, but I prefer the plastic ones personally, because I like to save mine up. There's really not much else to say about a giftcard. I hope my experience and pictures help give you an idea of what to expect in person. Please let me know if this helps. It gives me that little encouragement to continue to take the time to share my experiences.

title: No tamper proof! Comes sealed in plastic &envelope glued closed.
text:
I got this $10 giftcard as part of a bundle promotion during Cyber Monday. It came sealed in a plastic bag so you know it hasn't been tampered with. The black envelope comes glued closed, as well, which makes it great for gifting. This does have $10 on it, and was a nice incentive. If you're purchasing this outright to gift, I hope these pictures also help give you an idea of what to expect in person. I know there are many amazon gift card options to choose from, and I've bought many, so I just wanted to show what this particular gift card looks like in person. FYI...This is the hard cardboard style giftcard, which I've noticed is what seems to come in most options. Even the one's that come in the fancier box options on here. This is shinier. Some are matte. Most people probably don't care, but just thought I'd mention it.

*Tips if looking because of a bundle promo: Don't forget to add this in your cart along with the accompanying item if this is offered as a promotion. But...You must get to this page by clicking on the promotional add or it will not count. I originally tried just searching for a $10 gift card and adding it, but it would not deduct the discount when doing it that way. The link should be on the product page. Just click the words giftcard, and it should bring you here. I personally got mine as part of the Ring doorbell pro &Chime pro bundle on Cyber Monday. I actually thought it was going to be emailed for some reason, but it arrived in the box with the Chime Pro. I hope this review helps someone in some way.

title: A classy box, especially nice if you're not putting it in a card.
text:
I bought two of these from my daughter's volleyball team to their coaches for our volleyball banquet. In past years they've always received some type of volleyball item, and me and the other mom's thought we'd get them $50 gift cards instead so they can buy themselves whatever they want. I chose the gift box option, because it looks very classy and comes ready to gift if you want. I personally chose to put these in a little gift bag for a little mystery, and the fact they came with boxes really made this idea work.

They quality of the packaging was beautiful. The box has a beveled Amazon printed allover the entire top lid, including the sides. I do wish that the actual gift cards themselves were plastic like a credit card or how most other gift cards usually are. These are a thick stock paper/cardboard material. It still works, and for our purpose, I was happy. I would suggest getting a plastic option that doesn't come with a box if you're going to just unbox it and put this in an actual card. I almost bought these to do that, and figured at least I'd have a little gift box if needed. I now would recommend not doing that unless you are gifting in the box. I mean, you still could. It's just a gift card after all. The one meant for placing in a card will look higher quality for that purpose. But for handing someone a card with this gift box accompanying it would be a great idea, too.

This came in a sealed plastic bag to protect it, and so you can tell it hasn't been tampered with. It has an instruction card, which I placed in the lid, as well as a receipt incase there's any issues, which I folded and put under the gift cards. This is my experience, and I hope this helps with your gifting ideas and needs. I hope my pictures help give you an idea of to expect in person.

title: I love being able to add any amount to my balance, and not just a whole number.
text: I love being able to add any amount to my gift card balance. I had a prepaid credit card that was about to expire, and there wasn't an item for the exact amount down to the change that I wanted. I order from Amazon so much, that being able to put every penny on it's balance, is as good as still having my prepaid card, only this will never expire! Definitely, the way to go in this kind of situation.

title: Unique, Fun, better than a plain gift card!
text: [[VIDEOID:589ba0af0fdfdcb4de81473d0434bbb1]] These slider gift cards are beautiful. They are a unique style that I love. I ordered 14 of these for gifts and all slide smooth and look great.  They are a thinner but wider and longer than an iPhone 6,7,8 (see pics) so remember that if you plan to mail them in a card, the card will not be flat and you will need extra postage.  I got them for teachers and my nieces, as they are so much more unique than a plain gift card. Also, they stop when you pull them out so you cannot pull it apart without force and slide back in easy and smooth. I know another reviewer mentioned not having the amount printed on the card to know how much each was. I purchased both $25 and $50 penguin style cards and both had the amount printed on the front.

title: packaging was fine, however the picture is deceptive
text: Item arrived on time, packaging was fine, however the picture is deceptive. I ordered a $25 gift card picture says "gift box included", even has a picture of the attached flat gift card holder. No gift box or gift card holder was included. It was attached to a basic cardboard colored packaging. Pretty basic.

title: Perfect gift for a Teacher or any reader!
text: I love these bookmark gift cards! I purchased 12 of these for my children's teachers. I thinks it's the perfect gift for a teacher. They come in a nice protective ziploc style plastic protective cover and then the bookmark comes in a protective sleeve.  They are not as thick as the credit card style gift card, they are plastic but a nice thin style just like they should be for a book. Perfect!

title: and having them available all at one place it great. Saved me a lot of time and energy ...

This year I purchased 20 + gift cards for friends, teachers, relatives, etc. and having them available all at one place it great.  Saved me a lot of time and energy getting the variety that Amazon has on here.

title: Surprise Gift Card
text:
[[VIDEOID:82140569ad37d45ca06b452dd2cc34bd]] Imagine giving all presents to all family members except for one, then telling them you didn't give them one since they didn't help with the Christmas Tree decorations. They bust of crying, but you tell them their present was on the tree all along. To their surprise, there's a gift card hidden in one of the ornaments

First thing to note is that this is one of Amazon's Premium gift cards. $50 minimum on gift card for purchase.

Card stock on ornament is high quality. Held together by an overlap tab.

When you open the flap, you are greeted with a snowman with Christmas trees fanning out to the sides, and gift card on bottom

Gift card is attached via non residue adhesive

Gift card has a very basic teal background with Amazon Logo

Redeeming card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

title: Free Reindeer Ornament (and Box) with Gift Card Purchase
text:
[[VIDEOID:6b54148bd4781e6be110f9cfafe8b370]] First thing to note is that this is one of Amazon's Premium gift cards. $50 minimum on gift card for purchase. Gift cards easy to slide out and replace with another one if you think $50 is too much to give

Has a nice detachable reindeer ornament (via Velcro) to a box with ribbon design

Inside there's a gift card with checkered red design background with Amazon logos

No blank space for name of person of sender and receiver. Best to give to person directly (like proposing with a wedding ring) or combine it as part of other gift

Redeeming gift card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

Doesn't show the amount on the card seeing it's customizable on the website. But it does give a pack in slip of paper to verify amount.

title: Stockings too old fashioned?
text:
[[VIDEOID:eb7bd23f9aa57576889a0a3b89e5b3eb]]
First thing to note is that this is one of Amazon's Premium gift cards. $50 minimum on gift card for purchase. Gift cards easy to slide out and replace with another one if you think $50 is too much to give

Materials are really good from cardboard to ribbon. String with bells attached are superglued onto the bag. Everything thats white on the bag (except for string on bells) from Santa's beard to snowflakes are glittered

Opening flap is held together by velcro. When you lift up, it reveals card. Enough space inside to put a small gift stocking stuffer type gifts. Bag is 4inches deep and 4.25inches wide. Or you can leave nothing inside and have a few seconds of awkwardness

Amazon gift card itself is very basic. Just Amazon logos on all white background

Redeeming card is easy. Code is on back of the card, no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code or peeling off sticker. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

title: Multi-layed Gift
text:
[[VIDEOID:cdbb37ea266ddb8dd7c25de1509e36a7]] First thing to note is that this is one of Amazon's Premium gift cards. $50 minimum on gift card for purchase. Gift cards easy to slide out and replace with another one if you think $50 is too much to give to a baby that doesn't even know what s/he is getting.

Good gift to give if you don't know if your original gift would be good enough, or you're not sure if they have too much of the same thing...you know 2nd to 5th child, hand-me-down from friends and family, etc.

Materials are really good from cardboard to ribbon. The towel, sock and onesie are individual cardboard cutouts attached via double sided 3M (?) tape.

Opening flap is held together by velcro. When you lift up, it reveals card. Enough space inside to put a small gift like socks, pacifier, baby soap, cotton buds, nail clipper, baby jelly, wipes, etc. Or you can leave nothing inside and have a few seconds of awkwardness

Amazon gift card itself is very basic. Just Amazon logos on a zig-zag green backdrop

Redeeming card is easy. Code is on back of the card, no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code or peeling off sticker. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

title: Fun Gift Card Slider
text:
[[VIDEOID:362fcac7daee16967f9e95cee3ffa16c]] Great gift card slider for those who like to switch things up form other physical gift card distribution methods like boxes, bi-fold cards and/or envelopes

Middle section gives off a penguin stare, but changes into a smile-like eye appearance when tab is pulled.

When fully open; left side displays over a dozen penguins also giving a smile-like gester...with two balls and a dot (from original penguin eye stare).

Right side also have dozen plus penguins along with a gift card attached via non-residue like glue.

Back of the slider when fully expanded shows back of the penguins on the right and left side minus the eyes.

Sliding is very fluid. Can see a toddler having tons of fun sliding the card in and out

Redeeming card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

Overall, very unique designed card.

title: Got this for Lunar New Year
text:
Instead of handing out traditional red envelopes with cash for Lunar New Year, decided to hand out $10 amazon gift cards instead.

Doesn't have much to do with Lunar New Year themes with exception of the red coloring on the envelopes.

Can also be used for distributing in bulk at parties or other special occasions; giving every one the same gift so no one feels left out or start comparing which person got the better gift card design. Seeing the golden snow flake imprints, more catered towards the winter season.

Paper/cardboard for the envelope is of good quality. Has slight texture to it.

Card is held onto the envelope via light glue, which can be removed without leaving residue.

There is a cutout on back displaying UPC code or serial number.

Not really re-usable unless you have glue or double sided tape. But it does give off a premium first impression.

Gift card design itself is very basic; just white with red amazon logos on it. Has the amount specified on the corner which is a nice touch and don't keep the receiver guessing how much is inside

Redeeming card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

Overall, great gift card set to distribute in bulk

title: Not What I Expected
text:
Did not receive bookmark sleeve or the ribbon in stock photos

Code is on the back of the bookmark. From the photos thought it was a separate card or voucher. Fell odd when in use; when you flip it over, you see the gift card amount and bar codes. Guess it can be a motivator to finish a book, rewarding yourself after it's done, but only can be used once.

Code redemption is a scratch off which is disappointing. Thought they went pass that, and gone with a peel off design. Must have a coin or key handy.

If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

Shows the amount on the back of the bookmark, so no surprises.

Quality of the bookmark is good. Sturdy plastic. Slightly thinner than regular Amazon Gift Card. Is tear-proof, but can be cut with scissors.

Essentially just an Amazon Gift Card but in a different form factor: in a shape that can be used as a bookmark

title: Free Box with Gift Card Purchase
text:
Instead of being in a envelope and/or attached to a thank you, congratulations card; it's a card within premium looking gift box.

Box itself is very sturdy, has a premium look and feel to it.

The cloth and card holder inside; not so much. Cloth is wrapped around a plastic card holder that's glued to the box.

Cloth is very thin, but functional for what's it's intended for. If you swap in-and-out cards multiple times, the cloth may rip; but for initial first impression it won't.

Box has a slide out design to it. Has a stop gap so doesn't slide all the way out unless you intentionally use more force than you have to.

Very nice finger ribbon to pull out the contents like a drawer

Back of the box has a space for name of person of sender and receiver.

Includes UPC and Serial No. number and bar code if you find an error with the order.

Gift card design is very basic; just red with amazon logos on it. Redeeming card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option and align the boxes with the text code.

Doesn't show the amount on the card seeing it's customizable on the website. But it does give a pack in slip of paper to verify amount.

Aside from plastic card holder and cloth fabric being low quality; it still gives off a premium first impression

title: Free Socks (size 10-13) With Gift Card Purchase
text:
Update: They now added sock size in description

First thing to note is that the sock size is 10-13 US. Both my friend and I received the same size.
Description on product page states "Gift Card is affixed inside a gift box with a pair of Happy Socks (one size)" so I assume everyone will receive the same. If not, or want to confirm (if purchased) please put a comment to let others know.

Quality of the socks are standard; not too thin and not too sweat absorbent (like sport socks). Great for formal wear and those who want to draw attention to their feet, ankles, and/or shoes with the bright colors/patterns.

Happy socks usually go for around $16 a pair, so that's how much you are potentially saving

Gift card design is very basic; just red with amazon logos on it. Redeeming card is easy. There's a peel off sticker (instead of scratcher), so no need to worry about scratching off the text of the code. If you use the amazon app you can redeem the amount in seconds: click the camera option next to search bar, swipe up for gift card redeem photo option and align the boxes with the text code.

Box is very presentable; very good gift idea for a family or friends

Overall if you're going to spend money on Amazon throughout the year, or generous enough to give someone a pair of socks + $100+ gift card; then this is a excellent purchase; just keep in mind the sock size

text:
You get a free holiday teddy bear with a gift card purchase. Great incentive if you purchase items off Amazon regularly, or plan to give a $100+ gift card to a friend or family member.

Supposedly this is the 10th edition of the Holiday Teddy Bear. I started collecting these 2 years ago. Last year was a polar bear with a snow flake santa hat and gloves as opposed to grizzly bear with a Santa hat got this year. Year before that was a darker grizzly bear with a beanie.

Hat is not removable (unless you mess with the stitching). There is an ear under there for those wondering. The bear is super soft and huggable. Ideal for toddlers who get attached to soft objects during cold weather. There's also a amazon logo tattoo on it's left foot

Gift card is just a neckless attached to the bear. This time, the gift code is a peel off instead of a scratch off in back. Code is very easy to apply with Amazon app, just use the camera feature instead of the traditional input method.

Minimum gift card amount is $100. From previous years track record, best to get it early or the lower demonization may sell out

Overall if you're going to spend money on Amazon throughout the year or generous enough to give someone a bear + $100+ gift card; then this is a excellent purchase

title: Gift Card With Style
text:
Just your standard Amazon Giftcard inside a box that has the word 'Amazon' embossed on the front cover with an orange bow.

There are finger grooves for the front cover and inside the box for easy access.

Claiming the gift card once opened is also very easy. There's a peel off sticker so you don't need to bother with getting a coin or sharp metal object. Also you don't need to worry about scratching off the text for the gift card code.

If the person you gift it to have the Amazon app; they can click on the camera icon (after logging in) next to the search bar, and scan the code instead of typing each letter/number individually to claim the total amount.

Overall very simplistic design and a has great presentation. Great if you're tired of gifting gift cards in a standard envelope format.

title: Free Bear With Gift Card Purchase
text:
You get a free holiday teddy bear with a giftcard purchase. Great incentive if you purchase items off Amazon regularly or plan to give a $100+ giftcard to a friend or family member.

Supposedly this is the 9th edition of the Holiday Teddy Bear. I started collecting these last year. Last year was a grizzly bear with the beanie as opposed to the polar bear with a Santa hat and gloves we got this year. Another difference is that the 2015 model had the Amazon (dot) com logo on the left foot and the 2016 bear has just the amazon arrow logo.

Gloves and hat are not removable (unless you mess with the stitching). The bear is super soft and huggable. Ideal for toddlers who get attached to soft objects during cold weather.

Gift card is just a neckless attached to the bear. This time it's in the shape of a gift box which is nice. Gift code is a scratch off in back.

Overall if you're going to spend money on Amazon throughout the year or generous enough to give someone a bear + $100 to someone then this is a excellent purchase

** Note: I white out the UPC and Serial Number in the photos just in case i need to use it as reference later

title: Quality teddy bear from GUND...
text:
I have been collecting the Amazon annual holiday GUND Bears since they were first sold and as with previous years, this one is exceptional quality. The bear features the subtle Amazon crescent logo stitched on the left foot.
The gift card is tied around the bear's neck with a ribbon, which can easily be removed if you want to give the bear as a separate gift.

title: Classy, elegant presentation...
text:
Silly to say that I was impressed with this gift card but that's exactly what went through my mind when I opened it.
The card itself is shipped inside a small, elegant gift box that is adorned with an orange ribbon. The entire box is shrink wrapped and makes a nice gift presentation so feel confident if you need to ship this directly to the recipient rather than give to someone in person.
The box features the Amazon logo - very classy and suitable for both men and women of all ages.

title: Exceptional Gund quality, great gift or collectible..
text:
I've been ordering the Amazon holiday bears since they first came out. These are exceptional quality Gund Bears with an Amazon logo worked into the design. This year's bear - the ninth in the series - has the logo "smile" embroidered on the sole of the left foot. It is very soft and cuddly with red snowflake fleece for mittens and cap.
I spend a lot on Amazon over the holidays, mostly for local charities, so I end up using the gift card myself. The bear becomes a gift, again usually for a local charity. Win-win all around. Thank you Amazon!

title: Looking good when giving a gift
text: This box made a gift card appear special. I have ordered this version several times, using it for staff recognition, graduation, birthday and thank you. The box with bow makes the gift card very classy regardless of why it is being given and sex of the receiver.  It appears as if much more thought was given -- and thanks to Amazon comes delivered to you. Should an occasion for this come my way again, this design will be a quick shortcut I remember.

title: Seriously low stress method to complete a "wish you well" gift
text:
It was the perfect "wish you well as you go" gift. Ordered as part of a group goodbye gift to some of our team moving onto other adventures. Became the perfect gift as there was no worries about what to get, who needed more $$ for an appropriate gift or things not fitting. Amazon gift card allowed them to "store" electronically their treat, add other funds to it and select what they wanted to celebrate their next step in life. Even came wrapped! So easy I will offer to do the "goodbye gift" again.

Delay in delivery is the only reason these are not 5 stars -- as delivery person would not get out of their car to walk through an open gate to deliver.

title: Gift Cards in Bulk
text: I purchased 10 of these gift cards at $100 each. What you see is what you get. Each gift card came individually packaged in plastic wrap. I am pleased with my purchase and would recommend these to anyone interested in buying gift cards in bulk.

title: Gift Card With Exposed Claim Code
text: Who gets an Amazon gift card with an exposed claim code?  I've always either had to pull a thin covering off or scrape a covering off to reveal the code.  This gift card that I ordered directly from Amazon came with NO covering at all on it.  A call to customer service got me NO satisfaction.  This $100 gift card was purchased to be a Christmas gift.  The box by the way is great - very pretty.  Since it is 7 weeks until Christmas (and plenty of time for a potential Amazon employee thief to use the code they exposed) all I could figure out to do was put the card on MY own Amazon account and find something else to give that person for Christmas since I'm not sure it's safe to order gift cards directly from Amazon anymore!!  Last year around Christmas the Amazon deliveries were being slit open from the bottom so they could steal items they wanted, looks like this year Amazon employees want gift cards so they can choose their own merchandise!!

title: A nice Surprise!
text:
What a nice surprise! I purchased this gift card as a goof, not really having a great opinion of Red Lobster but giving it as a gift to someone (Frankie) who really wanted to try it. They went and I accompanied them and was pleasantly surprised at the quality of the food. The Bar Harbor Lobster Bake made it all worth while...plus...those biscuits...YUMMY!...AND a FREE Ceaser Salad! Can't beat it! Certainly changed my opinion!

All in all...Give this place a try...buy a gift card!

title: Taco Bell Gift Cards make a satisfying gift!
text:
What can I say, you can't go wrong with gift cards for occasions and this gift card is a favorite of college kids!

I gave this gift card as a gift and was really pleased with it. It is just a plain gift card but trust me, your recipient will love it! When I gave this card to my son, he was delighted. You know how many meals he can get especially if he eats off the dollar menu?! Taco Bell has a really nice dollar menu and the food is filling. Two burritos and a drink will cost you three dollars and will make a pretty filling and satisfying lunch!

All in all, he LOVED this gift card. There was no guessing the right size, getting the wrong item and even if he has a double of these, he'll still be happy! I highly recommend a Taco Bell card for anyone! Male, Female, old or young...it makes the perfect gift!

Disclaimer - I paid full price for this item and this is my honest and unbiased review. All opinions are my own based on personal experience.

title: Gift cards give great options!
text:
I ordered this gift card for my son. I like giving him gift cards so he can treat himself. If I handed over the cash, he would use it on bills or other necessities. This way he can enjoy a little treat. I know he loves the Panera soup and half sandwich deal that they have, which runs just under 10.00, so with this gift card he has about 5 meals! They do make the best Broccoli cheddar soup!

He can also use it on their bakery goods...as he loves their bread and cookies! At times, he'll buy a big loaf of that sour dough bread and Panera is kind enough to slice it up for him!

I'm going to put this in his stocking this year! I just know he is going to be THRILLED! I am positive my son will put this card to good use!! Santa is good!

title: DO NOT BUY SCAM
text: Do not buy this card, it is a scam. I purchased this as a gift for my son, he registered the card and it said it had the $200 balance that I had purchased. Within one day, before he could use it, there was a purchased made for software in the amount of $200 in New York. We live in South Carolina. Amazon was absolutely no help and refused to refund me. Total scam.
